ISLAMBAD — Wani rahoton U.N. yace fiye da 'yan ta'addan Pakistan 6,000 ne ke boye a Afghanistan, mafi akasari daga cikin kungiyar Taliban ta Pakistan da aka kama da alhakin kai hare haren sojan Pakistan da fararen hula.
Rahoton da aka fitar a wannan makon yace kungiyar, wacce aka fi sani da Tehreek-e-Taliban (TTP), ta danganta ta da kungiyar Afghanistan mai alaka da kungiyar Islamic State.
Wasu daga cikin 'yan kungiyar TTP sun ma shiga kungiyar mayakan IS, wadda ke da hedikwatarta a gabashin Afghanistan.
Gwamnatin Afghanistan bata amsa ba ranar Lahadi ga bukatar da jaridar Associated Press ta gabatar domin sharhi.
Rahoton yace IS a Afghanistan, da aka fi sani da IS a lardin Khorasan, ta yi ta bugun wuya ga jami'an tsaron Afghanistan har ma da dakarun Amurka da na NATO, har ma a wani lokaci da mayakan Taliban na Afghanistan suka kwace.
