Madhya Pradesh Babban Minista Shivraj Singh Chouhan, wanda a ranar Asabar ya tabbatar da cewa ya gwada tabbatacce ga COVID-19, tweeted Lahadi da safe ya ce yana “lafiya” kuma ya bayar da yabo ga ma'aikatan gaba a yaki da cutar coronavirus.
Babban Ministan ya kuma maimaita gargadin da ya yi daga jiya, lokacin da ya bukaci mutane da su bi jagorori, kamar kuncin rayuwa da kuma amfani da mayukan fuska.
“Ina lafiya, abokaina. Ƙaddamar da mayaƙan coronavirus, waɗanda ba su da haɗari da rayukansu, yana da kyau. Ina gaisawa da dukkan mayaƙan coronavirus na jihar,” Mr Chouhan tweeted daga asibitin Bhopal na Chirayu, inda aka shigar da shi jiya.
“Tsaya mita biyu, wanke hannayenka akai-akai kuma ku sa masks na fuska - waɗannan su ne manyan makamai da muke da su don kauce wa coronavirus. Ina roko ga dukkan mutane - ku yi amfani da wadannan makamai domin kanku da kuma 'yan uwanku,” inji shi.
“Dukkanku ku yi hankali, ku zauna lafiya da lafiya. Wannan shine abinda nake addu'a ga Allah,” Mr Chouhan ya kara da cewa.
A ranar Asabar Mr Chouhan ya tweeted cewa ya gwada tabbatacce ga cutar duk da kokarinsa na kauce wa kamuwa da cutar kuma ya yi gargadin cewa “kawai rashin kulawa ne ke gayyatar cutar coronavirus.”
Tweeting a wannan safiya Mr Chouhan ya ce duk da barazanar kamuwa da cutar akwai “babu bukatar tsoro” kuma ya bukaci wadanda ke nuna alamu da su samu kansu gwaji.
“Idan kana dauke da cutar, babu bukatar tsoro. Kada ku ɓoye bayyanar cututtuka amma ku gaya wa likitoci nan da nan, don haka za a iya fara magani. Yin magani na dai-dai zai sa ku lafiya,” inji shi.
Madhya Pradesh yana da kusan 27,000 COVID-19, wanda fiye da 7,600 suna aiki kuma 799 suna da nasaba da cutar.
